//v0.3.6 -POM

 option.POM_DEPTH_CPF = POM Depth
option.POM_DEPTH_CPF.comment = Depth of POM (3D Textures, or Parralax Occlusion Mapping). Standard is 0.25, most resource packs are designed for 0.25., setting higher may look broken. If higher breaks shadows, let me know.

 option.POM = POM  (3D Textures)
option.POM.comment = POM is Parallax Occlussion Mapping, a 3D Textures Technique. Options are in 'Better 3D Textures / POM. 0 -Off. 1 -On
value.POM.0 = Off
value.POM.1 = On

screen.POM=POM (3D Textures)
screen.POM.comment=Options for POM ( Parralax Occlussion Mapping, or 3D Textures )

 option.CTMPOMFIX_VERSION = CTM/POM-FIX Version
option.CTMPOMFIX_VERSION.comment = Applies my CTM/POM-FIXes to make better, seamless 3D Textures work, utilizing CTM & POM at the same time via like 11 different tiling techniques & Buffering Texture edges. Resource Packs have to be compatible to benefit. Info is on my Discord.
 option.INITIAL_POM_QUALITY_CPF = Initial POM Quality
option.INITIAL_POM_QUALITY_CPF.comment = Tracing Steps for POM. Too Low will look jank on things like grass with high detail, because it will miss blades. Refinement further increases quality, as long as this isn't too low and misses things. This is EXPONENTIALLY INCREASED by the 'Refinement Steps' Setting . Recommend 20+ but you don't need much more . 20 Initial with 5 Refine is like 1,000 Quality for the cost of 25
 option.REFINE_POM_CPF = Refinement Steps
option.REFINE_POM_CPF.comment = POM Refinement Steps . EXPONENTIAL QUALITY INCREASE FOR ALMOST FREE . 1 is ~4x quality at the cost of 1 quality . an extra 2x for every additional step . not great on very low quality for sharp stuff like grass, atleast 20 Initial Quality recommended . on some shaders low values may flicker
 option.POM_DISTANCE_CPF = POM Distance
option.POM_DISTANCE_CPF.comment = The distance to do POM from the camera, like only do it up close.
 option.FADE_IN_POM_CPF = Fade in POM
option.FADE_IN_POM_CPF.comment = Fade in POM by this much of the POM distance (in tenths). 
 option.POM_STYLE_CPF = POM Style
option.POM_STYLE_CPF.comment = 0 - sharp voxel cubes. 1 - tesselate by Texture Upscaling Resolution. 2 - smooth polygons 
 option.EXTEND_3D_SHADOWS_CPF = Extend 3D Shadows
option.EXTEND_3D_SHADOWS_CPF.comment = Depth writing for 3D Shadows, ao, 'Ray Traced Sun Shadows', etc in Textures out of POM range . 0 - off . 1 and 2 look the same, but either may be faster on your machine. I need to test if this still works, this is just from the CTMPOMFIX Port.
 option.CAPTURE_CPF_POM_DEPTH = Capture POM Depth (debug)
option.CAPTURE_CPF_POM_DEPTH.comment = don't change this
 option.CTMPOMFIX_INFO = CTMPOMFIX Info
option.CTMPOMFIX_INFO.comment = CTMPOMFIX overhauls 3D textures (POM) with special features, including fixing seams on 3D Connected Textures in resource packs formatted for it. in many cases it vastly improves quality/performance . Turn on POM, in OPtifine: turn off Video Settings/Quality/Better Grass
 option.CTMPOMFIX_Advanced_Options = CTMPOMFIX Advanced Options
option.CTMPOMFIX_Advanced_Options.comment = Advanced POM Options

 option.NOISE_STRENGTH_CPF = Noise Strength
option.NOISE_STRENGTH_CPF.comment = Strength of NOise Applied to POM
 option.FAR_FIXES_CPF = Far Fixes CPF
option.FAR_FIXES_CPF.comment = CTMPOMFIX OPTION: . just leave this on. hides buggy 3D overlays out of pom range and fixes UVs for textures using ctmpomfix mode 11 (some mods). also potentially improves performance in some cases
 option.FAST_TEX_READS_CPF = Fast Tex Reads
option.FAST_TEX_READS_CPF.comment = Suppossed to be faster, but isn't for me.
 option.DEPTH_WRITE_CPF = Depth Writing (READ)
option.DEPTH_WRITE_CPF.comment = Slow, this eats FPS.  §cIt is necesary for CTMPOMFIX v2 Features (CTM 3D Material Transitions between Blocks)§r. §e It is necesary for 3D Grass Shader §r . Turning off might break stuff
 option.SMOOTHING_NOISE_CPF = Smoothing Noise CPF
option.SMOOTHING_NOISE_CPF.comment =You can apply Noise to gently Smooth POM, it blurs it but reduces visible layers, especially at angles. Can also help de-flicker Pom Refinement if it's flickering, or cause it to flicker, or make 3D overlays to have seams.  0 - disable noise 1 - use noise . 2 - blur distance  3 - blur close to smooth
 option.UPSCALE_RESOLUTION_CPF = Upscale Resolution
option.UPSCALE_RESOLUTION_CPF.comment =Multplier for Upscaling and Texture filtering . 1 is infinite . these all cost the same, it's just visual preference
 option.NOISE_FUNCTION_CPF = Noise Function cpf
option.NOISE_FUNCTION_CPF.comment =Some shaders inject noise functions into POM, it helps hide layers but can blur . generally it's good . 0 - use a Shader Supplied noise function, if any . 1-x use other functions . 1+ may introduce some banding in pom until I find better alt noise functions
 option.DYNAMIC_QUALITY_CPF = Dynamic Quality
option.DYNAMIC_QUALITY_CPF.comment =lower pom quality at a distance . might improve performance . might make it worse . requires fade_in

 option.INCREASE_QUALITY_AT_ANGLES_CPF = Increase Quality at Angles
option.INCREASE_QUALITY_AT_ANGLES_CPF.comment = Increase the quality of POM at grazing angles . lower is better quality, but 0 is Off . this also limits the distance rays can go inside of blocks
 option.NOISE_STRENGTH_CPF = Noise Strength
option.NOISE_STRENGTH_CPF.comment =Some shaders inject noise functions into POM, it helps hide layers but can blur . Adjust its strength . This can improve or worsen POM appearance . This may create or solve flickering
 option.COLOR_MERGE_DIST_CPF = Color Merge Distance cpf
option.COLOR_MERGE_DIST_CPF.comment =Texture Filtering will use this value to blend or link colors that are this close to each other . Effect will vary per filter . just leave it or it will probably break texture filtering
 option.ALPHA_CUTOFF_CPF = Alpha Cutoff
option.ALPHA_CUTOFF_CPF.comment =Things more opaque than this will be solid in Texture Filtering . Thickens Grass at lower numbers
 
 
 option.SHADOW_BIAS_PL=Shadow Bias (Pixel Locked)
option.SHADOW_BIAS_PL.comment - Lower will have buggy artifacts, higher will have floating shadows - like space between things and thier shadows


	
